VNC Viewer:

    Uses the RFB (Remote Framebuffer Protocol) for remote screen sharing.
    Requires a VNC Server on the remote machine and is best for local network access.

Remote Desktop Connection (RDP):

    Built-in for Windows, optimized for Windows-to-Windows remote access.
    Supports encrypted connections with Network Level Authentication (NLA).

AnyDesk:

    Uses DeskRT codec for fast, low-latency remote access.
    Supports cross-platform access with secured encryption.

TeamViewer:

    No port forwarding needed, works through firewalls for easy remote access.
    Supports multi-user sessions, file transfer, and remote meetings.
